    {
      "id": "c6589bcca4e591fe78617fac5a8d82aec2b9471a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2022-04-21 00:29:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(2 comments)\n\nThomas,\nthanks for the update.  It would be useful if you added man page references to this \"lfs-hsm.1\" file so that \"man lfs-hsm_state\", etc. also worked:\n\n lfs-hsm_action.1:\n .so man1/lfs-hsm.1\n lfs-hsm_clear.1:\n .so man1/lfs-hsm.1\n\netc.\n\nAlso, I see that there are more HSM commands that exist, some of which are not listed here at all:\n\n $ lfs --help | grep hsm\n \"hsm_state\"\n \"hsm_set\"\n \"hsm_clear\"\n \"hsm_action\"\n \"hsm_archive\"\n \"hsm_restore\"\n \"hsm_release\"\n \"hsm_remove\"\n \"hsm_cancel\"\n\nIf the other lfs-hsm_* commands are sharing substantial text (same arguments, etc.) with the existing ones, they could also be added to \"lfs-hsm.1\" and have a reference file.  Otherwise, it would be better to add them with their own pages.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b08dbe70d6599fb19190b2a0e077151e36f0ecc0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2022-04-21 00:32:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nPS: if you are adding new lfs-hsm_*.1 man pages, please also add them to lustre/doc/Makefile.am so they are included in the packages.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
